A security guard was killed and his partner critically injured during a cash in transit heist in Pinetown today. The man sustainedÂ multiple injuries and before paramedics arrived.He was declared dead at the scene. Garrith Jamieson, spokesman for Rescue Care, said the second guard had sustained critical injuries and was stabilised on scene by Advanced Life Support Paramedics before being rushed to a nearby hospital for the urgent medical care he required.  It is unclear at this stage if money was taken but reports indicate that the remaining unknown number of suspects hijacked a Mercedes bus and fled the scene. The bus was found a few minutes later in Lahee Park. Police are investigating further. The affected road, Moodie Road, Hill Street and Dales Avenue, have been closed to traffic. Daily News